Script,RabbisRule
window.currentPBSScenario = 'RabbisRule';
window.currentPBSScenarioFilename = 'Rabbis_Rule';
console.log('PBS: Logging scenario selection for RabbisRule');
fetch('https://bba.harmonicsystems.com/api/scenario/select', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        'X-Client-Version': '1.0.0'
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
        scenario: 'RabbisRule',
        user: whoAmI() || 'anonymous'
    })
}).then(function(r){ console.log('PBS: Server response', r.status); }).catch(function(e){ console.log('PBS: Fetch error', e); });
setDealerCode(`

/*
convention-card-ns: Basic-Bridge
convention-card-ew: Basic-Bridge
auction-filter: Auction.....\n(1S +Pass +2S +Pass\n4S +Pass +Pass +Pass|1S +Pass +3S +Pass\n4S +Pass +Pass +Pass|1S +Pass +4S +Pass\nPass +Pass)
*/
// Predeal the safety-play layout. Declarer's trump tops + diamond AQ +
// one heart stopper. Dummy: spade Q for an extra trump trick + club K.
// West: stiff K of diamonds. East: long hearts headed by KQ.
predeal south SAK,HA,DAQ
predeal north CK
predeal west  DK
predeal east  HKQ

dealer south

// ----- Declarer (South) — 1S opener with 6 spades -----
sHcp     = hcp(south) > 16 and hcp(south) < 20
sSpades  = spades(south) == 6                // 6-card suit for trump dominance
sDiamonds = diamonds(south) > 3 and diamonds(south) < 6   // AQ + 2-3 small
southHand = sHcp and sSpades and sDiamonds

// ----- Dummy (North) — game-raising response -----
nHcp     = hcp(north) > 5 and hcp(north) < 10
nSpades  = spades(north) > 2 and spades(north) < 5   // 3-card support
nDiamonds = diamonds(north) > 1 and diamonds(north) < 5   // 2-4
northHand = nHcp and nSpades and nDiamonds

// ----- West — STIFF K of diamonds -----
wDiamonds = diamonds(west) == 1           // K alone
wHcp      = hcp(west) < 11
westHand = wDiamonds and wHcp

// ----- East — long hearts headed by KQ -----
eHearts   = hearts(east) > 4
eHcp      = hcp(east) < 11
eastHand = eHearts and eHcp

southHand and northHand and westHand and eastHand

action printoneline,
average "West stiff K (forced)  " 100 * (diamonds(west) == 1),
average "East 5+ hearts (forced)" 100 * (hearts(east) > 4),
average "South 6 spades         " 100 * (spades(south) == 6),
average "South HCP              "       hcp(south),
average "North HCP              "       hcp(north),
`, "S", true)
Script
Button,Rabbi\'s Rule,\n\
--- Rabbi's Rule (4!S) — safety play，drop the singleton King\n\
"When the King is singleton，play the Ace." This is a SAFETY PLAY.\n\
\n\
South opens 1!S and partnership reaches 4!S.\n\
\n\
Declarer has 10 sure tricks WITHOUT touching the diamond Queen — solid\n\
trumps，the heart Ace，and a club winner — but the diamond suit is the\n\
trap.\n\
\n\
• AQxxx in declarer opposite xxx in dummy. The King is missing.\n\
• West has the SINGLETON K. East has Jxxx.\n\
• Take the safety play: cash the Ace. The stiff K drops; the Q is\n\
  established as a small bonus，but more importantly you never give up\n\
  the lead. Contract makes.\n\
• Try for an overtrick by finessing: lead toward the AQ and play the Q.\n\
  West's K wins. Now West can put East in，and East cashes long hearts.\n\
  Contract goes down — at least 1，sometimes more.\n\
\n\
The lesson: COUNT your top tricks before deciding any finesse. If you\n\
already have enough to make，the finesse is gratuitous risk — and Rabbi's\n\
Rule (cash the Ace) is the safer play.\n\
\n\
Things to think about:\n\
• What's your trick count BEFORE you touch diamonds?\n\
• Where is the danger hand for cashing — east or west?\n\
• Does the auction (silent opps) say anything about diamond distribution?\n\
%RabbisRule%
